'''Chasma''' (pl. ''chasmata'') is a [[Greek language|Greek]] word used in [[planetary geology]] to refer to long, narrow, steep sided depressions on other [[planet]]s and [[natural satellite|moons]].

== See also ==
* [[Chasma Spring|Chasma]] means ''Water Spring'' in [[Persian language|Persian]] and [[Urdu language|Urdu]].
* [[Chashma (Pakistan)|Chasma]] is a city in Pakistan.

